ne\",\"brown\",\"white\",\"none\",\"none\",\"white\",\"white\",\"black\",\"white\",\"green\",\"gray\",\"brown\",\"black\",\"red\",\"brown\",\"none\",\"brown\",\"black\",\"white\",\"yellow\",\"purple\",\"white\",\"yellow\",\"white\",\"white\",\"white\",\"brown\",\"yellow\",\"none\",\"white\",\"orange\",\"brown\",\"gray\",\"white\",\"none\",\"pink\",\"orange\",\"brown\",\"white\",\"purple\",\"white\",\"white\",\"white\",\"gray\",\"white\",\"brown\",\"white\",\"orange\",\"orange\",\"white\",\"brown\",\"white\",\"gray\",\"yellow\",\"yellow\",\"white\",\"gray\",\"white\",\"brown\",\"white\",\"white\",\"none\",\"white\",\"white\",\"white\",\"yellow\",\"white\",\"pink\",\"pink\",\"white\",\"brown\",\"green\",\"white\",\"black\"],\"stem_height\":[10.81,5.2,6.09,4.89,3.84,10.51,13.15,8.07,9.83,2.69,4.56,10.87,9.02,6.85,8.4,3.3,7.91,6.01,4.98,1.4,6.54,4.87,7.28,5.28,7.85,6.12,6.32,9.47,7.52,12.52,3.99,6.65,5.04,0,5.35,6.46,2.57,6.13,6.78,9.12,5.16,7.21,6.4,7.42,4.06,7.97,4.61,8.4,5.34,6.07,15.57,8.73,4.24,14.94,8.29,5.48,6.88,5.31,6.94,5.32,5.41,4.67,5.12,4.88,16.52,8.27,6.57,4.71,4.95,6.62,4.88,4.68,4.98,2.55,3.4,13.91,5.04,8.23,6.46,0,5.01,5.36,6.28,5.23,6.7,6.81,11.73,5.76,5.5,4.96,5.55,0,8.62,8.56,8.76,5.55,4.63,0,5.22,8.3,4.45,4.11,6.42,7.38,5.92,6.29,4.49,5.52,4.83,3.42,6.42,7.85,6.45,1.61,13.78,6.64,6.01,14.65,0,4.31,5.81,5.37,4.48,2.82,3.95,5.89,4.77,6.34,7.72,11.44,4.43,3.16,2.94,5.56,8.09,16.63,12.75,3.12,8.74,5.72,3.63,8.3,6.35,4.32,7.73,5.72,5.12,5.9,3.76,15.91],\"stem_width\":[19.22,11.46,13.92,1.08,2.47,14.33,13.24,9.78,12.77,8.04,12.34,16.28,17.31,9.41,23.88,16.78,5.41,31.94,3.25,13.44,10.56,2.9,14.9,3.31,2.7,18.15,3.52,13.71,17.94,12.08,5.8,6.78,5.25,0,23.33,16.28,4.3,3.76,34.32,17.16,13.28,21.81,48.84,12.78,2.52,9.28,3.96,2.44,6.59,34.02,7.64,16.59,1.08,7.04,10.28,2.37,6.73,6.86,15.38,2.52,9.17,5.55,2.65,5.01,18.3,15.18,6.83,13.99,5.71,12.36,24.34,17.1,23.7,6.62,9.11,16.53,14.56,24.95,4.73,0,26.76,10.43,13.37,2.62,9.91,8.22,22.58,6.68,12.3,5.69,6.43,0,8.73,9.4,13.69,29.27,5.29,0,9.61,23.29,7.93,2.38,6.54,12.94,21.15,18.39,6.67,26.16,13.51,8.59,20.79,30.13,17.34,2.21,13.15,8.57,9.38,7.09,0,6.53,6.73,2.71,12.48,6.29,7.72,6.34,1.72,22.85,8.46,10.75,12.07,5.35,1.41,10.33,9.74,9.28,36.76,24.46,13.2,0.98,3.23,18.61,9.82,3.02,4.17,10.52,10.77,6.93,6.5,18.23]},\"columns\":[{\"id\":\"class\",\"name\":\"class\",\"type\":\"factor\"},{\"id\":\"cap_diameter\",\"name\":\"cap_diameter\",\"type\":\"numeric\"},{\"id\":\"cap_shape\",\"name\":\"cap_shape\",\"type\":\"factor\"},{\"id\":\"cap_surface\",\"name\":\"cap_surface\",\"type\":\"factor\"},{\"id\":\"cap_color\",\"name\":\"cap_color\",\"type\":\"factor\"},{\"id\":\"does_bruise_or_bleed\",\"name\":\"does_bruise_or_bleed\",\"type\":\"logical\"},{\"id\":\"gill_attachment\",\"name\":\"gill_attachment\",\"type\":\"factor\"},{\"id\":\"gill_color\",\"name\":\"gill_color\",\"type\":\"factor\"},{\"id\":\"stem_height\",\"name\":\"stem_height\",\"type\":\"numeric\"},{\"id\":\"stem_width\",\"name\":\"stem_width\",\"type\":\"numeric\"}],\"theme\":{\"color\":\"hsl(233, 9%, 87%)\",\"backgroundColor\":\"hsl(233, 9%, 19%)\",\"borderColor\":\"hsl(233, 9%, 22%)\",\"stripedColor\":\"hsl(233, 12%, 22%)\",\"highlightColor\":\"hsl(233, 12%, 24%)\",\"inputStyle\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"hsl(233, 9%, 25%)\"},\"selectStyle\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"hsl(233, 9%, 25%)\"},\"pageButtonHoverStyle\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"hsl(233, 9%, 25%)\"},\"pageButtonActiveStyle\":{\"backgroundColor\":\"hsl(233, 9%, 28%)\"}},\"dataKey\":\"5a520e4cd7a0414adf9a81dd87e7cb3f\"},\"children\":[]},\"class\":\"reactR_markup\"},\"evals\":[],\"jsHooks\":[]}</script>\n```\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n</div>\n\n\n## Create ggplots\n\nTo create a patchwork we need a few ggplots saved as objects first.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\n#Bar chart\nbarchart <- mushroom_tbl |> \n    ggplot2::ggplot(aes(x = class)) + \n    ggplot2::geom_bar()\n#Histogram\nhistogram <- mushroom_tbl |> \n    ggplot2::ggplot(aes(x = cap_diameter)) + \n    ggplot2::geom_histogram()\n#Line graph\nline <- mushroom_tbl |> \n    ggplot2::ggplot(aes(x = stem_width, y = stem_height)) + \n    ggplot2::geom_line()\n#Scatter plot\npoint <- mushroom_tbl |> \n    ggplot2::ggplot(aes(x = stem_width, y = stem_height)) + \n    ggplot2::geom_point()\n#Box plot\nbox <- mushroom_tbl |> \n    ggplot2::ggplot(aes(x = class, y = cap_diameter)) + \n    ggplot2::geom_boxplot()\n```\n:::\n\n\n## Horizontal\n\nTo create a graphic with plots side by side you can use `|`.\n\nThe below code creates a graphic with the line and point ggplots side by side.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nline | point\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](patchwork_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-6-1.png){width=979.2}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Vertical\n\nTo put one plot on top of another in a graphic you can use `/`\n\nThe below code creates a graphic with the barchart above the histogram.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nbarchart / histogram\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n`stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value `binwidth`.\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](patchwork_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-7-1.png){width=979.2}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Grid\n\nA more complicated graphic can be created by mixing the use of `|` and `/`.\nIf doing this it is common to put all the plots in the same row in brackets `()`.\n\nExample code and plot below.\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\n(barchart | histogram | box) / (line | point)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n`stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value `binwidth`.\n```\n\n\n:::\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](patchwork_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-8-1.png){width=979.2}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n## Save as a file\n\nYou can save a patchworked graphic with [`ggsave()`](/ggplot2/ggsave.qmd)\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npatchwork_ggplot <- (barchart | histogram | box) / (line | point)\nggplot2::ggsave(filename=\"images/patchwork.png\", plot=patchwork_ggplot,\n                device=\"png\", units=\"mm\", height=200, width = 200)\n```\n:::\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stderr}\n\n```\n`stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value `binwidth`.\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\nThe PNG file contains the following image:\n\n<center>\n![](images/patchwork.png){style=\"width:700px\"}\n</center>\n\n## Layout\n\nAs you may have noticed when laying out the plots on a graphic `patchwork` will divide spaces equally between the rows and the columns within each row.\nIn the last plot:\n\n- Each of the 2 rows are given 50% of the height\n- The first row has 3 plots so each plot is given a third of the graphic width\n- The second row has 2 plots so each plot is given a half of the graphic width\n\nThere are many ways to control the layout.\nTo see these various methods please check the following link:\n\n[Patchwork controlling layouts webpage](https://patchwork.data-imaginist.com/articles/guides/layout.html)",
